        <citation_list><citation key="ref1"><unstructured_citation>Qualimap%202:%20advanced%20multi-sample%20quality%20control%20for%20high-throughput%20sequencing%20data, Okonechnikov,%20Konstantin%20and%20Conesa,%20Ana%20and%20Garc%C4%B1%CC%81a-Alcalde,%20Fernando, Department%20of%20Molecular%20Biology,%20Max%20Planck%20Institute%20for%20Infection%20Biology,%20D-10117,%20Berlin,%20Germany.%20Genomics%20of%20Gene%20Expression%20Lab,%20Centro%20de%20Investigaci%C3%B3n%20Pr%C4%B1%CC%81ncipe%20Felipe,%2046012,%20Valencia,%20Spain%20and%20Microbiology%20and%20Cell%20Science%20Department,%20Institute%20for%20Food%20and%20Agricultural%20Research,%20University%20of%20Florida%20at%20Gainesville,%20FL%2032611-0700,%20USA., MOTIVATION:%20Detection%20of%20random%20errors%20and%20systematic%20biases%20is%20a%20crucial%20step%20of%20a%20robust%20pipeline%20for%20processing%20high-throughput%20sequencing%20(HTS)%20data.%20Bioinformatics%20software%20tools%20capable%20of%20performing%20this%20task%20are%20available,%20either%20for%20general%20analysis%20of%20HTS%20data%20or%20targeted%20to%20a%20specific%20sequencing%20technology.%20However,%20most%20of%20the%20existing%20QC%20instruments%20only%20allow%20processing%20of%20one%20sample%20at%20a%20time.%20RESULTS:%20Qualimap%202%20represents%20a%20next%20step%20in%20the%20QC%20analysis%20of%20HTS%20data.%20Along%20with%20comprehensive%20single-sample%20analysis%20of%20alignment%20data,%20it%20includes%20new%20modes%20that%20allow%20simultaneous%20processing%20and%20comparison%20of%20multiple%20samples.%20As%20with%20the%20first%20version,%20the%20new%20features%20are%20available%20via%20both%20graphical%20and%20command%20line%20interface.%20Additionally,%20it%20includes%20a%20large%20number%20of%20improvements%20proposed%20by%20the%20user%20community.%20AVAILABILITY%20AND%20IMPLEMENTATION:%20The%20implementation%20of%20the%20software%20along%20with%20documentation%20is%20freely%20available%20at%20http://www.qualimap.org.%20CONTACT:%20meyer@mpiib-berlin.mpg.de%20SUPPLEMENTARY%20INFORMATION:%20Supplementary%20data%20are%20available%20at%20Bioinformatics%20online., Bioinformatics, academic.oup.com, 32, 2, 292%E2%80%93294, jan, 2016, http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btv566, en, 1</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref2"><unstructured_citation>FastQC:%20a%20quality%20control%20tool%20for%20high%20throughput%20sequence%20data, Bioinformatics,%20Babraham, Cambridge,%20UK:%20Babraham%20Institute, 2011</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref3"><unstructured_citation>BEDTools:%20a%20flexible%20suite%20of%20utilities%20for%20comparing%20genomic%20features, Quinlan,%20Aaron%20R%20and%20Hall,%20Ira%20M, Department%20of%20Biochemistry%20and%20Molecular%20Genetics,%20University%20of%20Virginia%20School%20of%20Medicine,%20Charlottesville,%20VA%2022908,%20USA.%20aaronquinlan@gmail.com, MOTIVATION:%20Testing%20for%20correlations%20between%20different%20sets%20of%20genomic%20features%20is%20a%20fundamental%20task%20in%20genomics%20research.%20However,%20searching%20for%20overlaps%20between%20features%20with%20existing%20web-based%20methods%20is%20complicated%20by%20the%20massive%20datasets%20that%20are%20routinely%20produced%20with%20current%20sequencing%20technologies.%20Fast%20and%20flexible%20tools%20are%20therefore%20required%20to%20ask%20complex%20questions%20of%20these%20data%20in%20an%20efficient%20manner.%20RESULTS:%20This%20article%20introduces%20a%20new%20software%20suite%20for%20the%20comparison,%20manipulation%20and%20annotation%20of%20genomic%20features%20in%20Browser%20Extensible%20Data%20(BED)%20and%20General%20Feature%20Format%20(GFF)%20format.%20BEDTools%20also%20supports%20the%20comparison%20of%20sequence%20alignments%20in%20BAM%20format%20to%20both%20BED%20and%20GFF%20features.%20The%20tools%20are%20extremely%20efficient%20and%20allow%20the%20user%20to%20compare%20large%20datasets%20(e.g.%20next-generation%20sequencing%20data)%20with%20both%20public%20and%20custom%20genome%20annotation%20tracks.%20BEDTools%20can%20be%20combined%20with%20one%20another%20as%20well%20as%20with%20standard%20UNIX%20commands,%20thus%20facilitating%20routine%20genomics%20tasks%20as%20well%20as%20pipelines%20that%20can%20quickly%20answer%20intricate%20questions%20of%20large%20genomic%20datasets.%20AVAILABILITY%20AND%20IMPLEMENTATION:%20BEDTools%20was%20written%20in%20C++.%20Source%20code%20and%20a%20comprehensive%20user%20manual%20are%20freely%20available%20at%20http://code.google.com/p/bedtools%20CONTACT:%20aaronquinlan@gmail.com;%20imh4y@virginia.edu%20SUPPLEMENTARY%20INFORMATION:%20Supplementary%20data%20are%20available%20at%20Bioinformatics%20online., Bioinformatics, 26, 6, 841%E2%80%93842, mar, 2010, http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btq033, en, 3</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref4"><unstructured_citation>Aligning%20sequence%20reads,%20clone%20sequences%20and%20assembly%20contigs%20with%20BWA-MEM, Li,%20Heng, Summary:%20BWA-MEM%20is%20a%20new%20alignment%20algorithm%20for%20aligning%20sequence%20reads%20or%20long%20query%20sequences%20against%20a%20large%20reference%20genome%20such%20as%20human.%20It%20automatically%20chooses%20between%20local%20and%20end-to-end%20alignments,%20supports%20paired-end%20reads%20and%20performs%20chimeric%20alignment.%20The%20algorithm%20is%20robust%20to%20sequencing%20errors%20and%20applicable%20to%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20sequence%20lengths%20from%2070bp%20to%20a%20few%20megabases.%20For%20mapping%20100bp%20sequences,%20BWA-MEM%20shows%20better%20performance%20than%20several%20state-of-art%20read%20aligners%20to%20date.%20Availability%20and%20implementation:%20BWA-MEM%20is%20implemented%20as%20a%20component%20of%20BWA,%20which%20is%20available%20at%20http://github.com/lh3/bwa.%20Contact:%20hengli@broadinstitute.org, mar, 2013, http://arxiv.org/abs/1303.3997, arXiv, q-bio.GN, 1303.3997, 3</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref5"><unstructured_citation>BigDataScript:%20a%20scripting%20language%20for%20data%20pipelines, Cingolani,%20Pablo%20and%20Sladek,%20Rob%20and%20Blanchette,%20Mathieu, McGill%20University%20School%20of%20Computer%20Science,%203480%20University%20Street,%20Montreal,%20Qu%C3%A9bec%20H3A%200E9%20and%20McGill%20University%20and%20G%C3%A9nome%20Qu%C3%A9bec%20Innovation%20Centre,%20740%20Dr.%20Penfield%20Avenue,%20Montr%C3%A9al,%20Qu%C3%A9bec%20H3A%200G1,%20Canada%20McGill%20University%20School%20of%20Computer%20Science,%203480%20University%20Street,%20Montreal,%20Qu%C3%A9bec%20H3A%200E9%20and%20McGill%20University%20and%20G%C3%A9nome%20Qu%C3%A9bec%20Innovation%20Centre,%20740%20Dr.%20Penfield%20Avenue,%20Montr%C3%A9al,%20Qu%C3%A9bec%20H3A%200G1,%20Canada.%20McGill%20University%20School%20of%20Computer%20Science,%203480%20University%20Street,%20Montreal,%20Qu%C3%A9bec%20H3A%200E9%20and%20McGill%20University%20and%20G%C3%A9nome%20Qu%C3%A9bec%20Innovation%20Centre,%20740%20Dr.%20Penfield%20Avenue,%20Montr%C3%A9al,%20Qu%C3%A9bec%20H3A%200G1,%20Canada., MOTIVATION:%20The%20analysis%20of%20large%20biological%20datasets%20often%20requires%20complex%20processing%20pipelines%20that%20run%20for%20a%20long%20time%20on%20large%20computational%20infrastructures.%20We%20designed%20and%20implemented%20a%20simple%20script-like%20programming%20language%20with%20a%20clean%20and%20minimalist%20syntax%20to%20develop%20and%20manage%20pipeline%20execution%20and%20provide%20robustness%20to%20various%20types%20of%20software%20and%20hardware%20failures%20as%20well%20as%20portability.%20RESULTS:%20We%20introduce%20the%20BigDataScript%20(BDS)%20programming%20language%20for%20data%20processing%20pipelines,%20which%20improves%20abstraction%20from%20hardware%20resources%20and%20assists%20with%20robustness.%20Hardware%20abstraction%20allows%20BDS%20pipelines%20to%20run%20without%20modification%20on%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20computer%20architectures,%20from%20a%20small%20laptop%20to%20multi-core%20servers,%20server%20farms,%20clusters%20and%20clouds.%20BDS%20achieves%20robustness%20by%20incorporating%20the%20concepts%20of%20absolute%20serialization%20and%20lazy%20processing,%20thus%20allowing%20pipelines%20to%20recover%20from%20errors.%20By%20abstracting%20pipeline%20concepts%20at%20programming%20language%20level,%20BDS%20simplifies%20implementation,%20execution%20and%20management%20of%20complex%20bioinformatics%20pipelines,%20resulting%20in%20reduced%20development%20and%20debugging%20cycles%20as%20well%20as%20cleaner%20code.%20AVAILABILITY%20AND%20IMPLEMENTATION:%20BigDataScript%20is%20available%20under%20open-source%20license%20at%20http://pcingola.github.io/BigDataScript., Bioinformatics, 31, 1, 10%E2%80%9316, jan, 2015, http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btu595, en, 1</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref6"><unstructured_citation>HISAT:%20a%20fast%20spliced%20aligner%20with%20low%20memory%20requirements, Kim,%20Daehwan%20and%20Langmead,%20Ben%20and%20Salzberg,%20Steven%20L, 1]%20Center%20for%20Computational%20Biology,%20McKusick-Nathans%20Institute%20of%20Genetic%20Medicine,%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University%20School%20of%20Medicine,%20Baltimore,%20Maryland,%20USA.%20[2]%20Department%20of%20Biostatistics,%20Bloomberg%20School%20of%20Public%20Health,%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University,%20Baltimore,%20Maryland,%20USA.%201]%20Center%20for%20Computational%20Biology,%20McKusick-Nathans%20Institute%20of%20Genetic%20Medicine,%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University%20School%20of%20Medicine,%20Baltimore,%20Maryland,%20USA.%20[2]%20Department%20of%20Biostatistics,%20Bloomberg%20School%20of%20Public%20Health,%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University,%20Baltimore,%20Maryland,%20USA.%20[3]%20Department%20of%20Computer%20Science,%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University,%20Baltimore,%20Maryland,%20USA., HISAT%20(hierarchical%20indexing%20for%20spliced%20alignment%20of%20transcripts)%20is%20a%20highly%20efficient%20system%20for%20aligning%20reads%20from%20RNA%20sequencing%20experiments.%20HISAT%20uses%20an%20indexing%20scheme%20based%20on%20the%20Burrows-Wheeler%20transform%20and%20the%20Ferragina-Manzini%20(FM)%20index,%20employing%20two%20types%20of%20indexes%20for%20alignment:%20a%20whole-genome%20FM%20index%20to%20anchor%20each%20alignment%20and%20numerous%20local%20FM%20indexes%20for%20very%20rapid%20extensions%20of%20these%20alignments.%20HISAT%E2%80%99s%20hierarchical%20index%20for%20the%20human%20genome%20contains%2048,000%20local%20FM%20indexes,%20each%20representing%20a%20genomic%20region%20of%20%E2%88%BC64,000%20bp.%20Tests%20on%20real%20and%20simulated%20data%20sets%20showed%20that%20HISAT%20is%20the%20fastest%20system%20currently%20available,%20with%20equal%20or%20better%20accuracy%20than%20any%20other%20method.%20Despite%20its%20large%20number%20of%20indexes,%20HISAT%20requires%20only%204.3%20gigabytes%20of%20memory.%20HISAT%20supports%20genomes%20of%20any%20size,%20including%20those%20larger%20than%204%20billion%20bases., Nat.%20Methods, 12, 4, 357%E2%80%93360, apr, 2015, http://dx.doi.org/10.1038/nmeth.3317, en, 4</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref7"><unstructured_citation>The%20Sequence%20Alignment/Map%20format%20and%20SAMtools, Li,%20Heng%20and%20Handsaker,%20Bob%20and%20Wysoker,%20Alec%20and%20Fennell,%20Tim%20and%20Ruan,%20Jue%20and%20Homer,%20Nils%20and%20Marth,%20Gabor%20and%20Abecasis,%20Goncalo%20and%20Durbin,%20Richard%20and%201000%20Genome%20Project%20Data%20Processing%20Subgroup, Wellcome%20Trust%20Sanger%20Institute,%20Wellcome%20Trust%20Genome%20Campus,%20Cambridge,%20CB10%201SA,%20UK,%20Broad%20Institute%20of%20MIT%20and%20Harvard,%20Cambridge,%20MA%2002141,%20USA., SUMMARY:%20The%20Sequence%20Alignment/Map%20(SAM)%20format%20is%20a%20generic%20alignment%20format%20for%20storing%20read%20alignments%20against%20reference%20sequences,%20supporting%20short%20and%20long%20reads%20(up%20to%20128%20Mbp)%20produced%20by%20different%20sequencing%20platforms.%20It%20is%20flexible%20in%20style,%20compact%20in%20size,%20efficient%20in%20random%20access%20and%20is%20the%20format%20in%20which%20alignments%20from%20the%201000%20Genomes%20Project%20are%20released.%20SAMtools%20implements%20various%20utilities%20for%20post-processing%20alignments%20in%20the%20SAM%20format,%20such%20as%20indexing,%20variant%20caller%20and%20alignment%20viewer,%20and%20thus%20provides%20universal%20tools%20for%20processing%20read%20alignments.%20AVAILABILITY:%20http://samtools.sourceforge.net., Bioinformatics, 25, 16, 2078%E2%80%932079, aug, 2009, http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btp352, en, 8</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref8"><unstructured_citation>MultiQC:%20summarize%20analysis%20results%20for%20multiple%20tools%20and%20samples%20in%20a%20single%20report, Ewels,%20Philip%20and%20Magnusson,%20M%C3%A5ns%20and%20Lundin,%20Sverker%20and%20K%C3%A4ller,%20Max, Department%20of%20Biochemistry%20and%20Biophysics,%20Science%20for%20Life%20Laboratory,%20Stockholm%20University,%20Stockholm%20106%2091,%20Sweden.%20Department%20of%20Molecular%20Medicine%20and%20Surgery,%20Science%20for%20Life%20Laboratory,%20Center%20for%20Molecular%20Medicine,%20Karolinska%20Institutet,%20Stockholm,%20Sweden.%20Science%20for%20Life%20Laboratory,%20School%20of%20Biotechnology,%20Division%20of%20Gene%20Technology,%20Royal%20Institute%20of%20Technology,%20Stockholm,%20Sweden., MOTIVATION:%20Fast%20and%20accurate%20quality%20control%20is%20essential%20for%20studies%20involving%20next-generation%20sequencing%20data.%20Whilst%20numerous%20tools%20exist%20to%20quantify%20QC%20metrics,%20there%20is%20no%20common%20approach%20to%20flexibly%20integrate%20these%20across%20tools%20and%20large%20sample%20sets.%20Assessing%20analysis%20results%20across%20an%20entire%20project%20can%20be%20time%20consuming%20and%20error%20prone;%20batch%20effects%20and%20outlier%20samples%20can%20easily%20be%20missed%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20analysis.%20RESULTS:%20We%20present%20MultiQC,%20a%20tool%20to%20create%20a%20single%20report%20visualising%20output%20from%20multiple%20tools%20across%20many%20samples,%20enabling%20global%20trends%20and%20biases%20to%20be%20quickly%20identified.%20MultiQC%20can%20plot%20data%20from%20many%20common%20bioinformatics%20tools%20and%20is%20built%20to%20allow%20easy%20extension%20and%20customization.%20AVAILABILITY%20AND%20IMPLEMENTATION:%20MultiQC%20is%20available%20with%20an%20GNU%20GPLv3%20license%20on%20GitHub,%20the%20Python%20Package%20Index%20and%20Bioconda.%20Documentation%20and%20example%20reports%20are%20available%20at%20http://multiqc.info%20CONTACT:%20phil.ewels@scilifelab.se., Bioinformatics, 32, 19, 3047%E2%80%933048, oct, 2016, http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btw354, en, 10</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref9"><unstructured_citation>featureCounts:%20an%20efficient%20general%20purpose%20program%20for%20assigning%20sequence%20reads%20to%20genomic%20features, Liao,%20Yang%20and%20Smyth,%20Gordon%20K%20and%20Shi,%20Wei, Bioinformatics%20Division,%20The%20Walter%20and%20Eliza%20Hall%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Research,%201G%20Royal%20Parade,%20Parkville,%20VIC%203052,%20Department%20of%20Computing%20and%20Information%20Systems%20and%20Department%20of%20Mathematics%20and%20Statistics,%20The%20University%20of%20Melbourne,%20Parkville,%20VIC%203010,%20Australia., MOTIVATION:%20Next-generation%20sequencing%20technologies%20generate%20millions%20of%20short%20sequence%20reads,%20which%20are%20usually%20aligned%20to%20a%20reference%20genome.%20In%20many%20applications,%20the%20key%20information%20required%20for%20downstream%20analysis%20is%20the%20number%20of%20reads%20mapping%20to%20each%20genomic%20feature,%20for%20example%20to%20each%20exon%20or%20each%20gene.%20The%20process%20of%20counting%20reads%20is%20called%20read%20summarization.%20Read%20summarization%20is%20required%20for%20a%20great%20variety%20of%20genomic%20analyses%20but%20has%20so%20far%20received%20relatively%20little%20attention%20in%20the%20literature.%20RESULTS:%20We%20present%20featureCounts,%20a%20read%20summarization%20program%20suitable%20for%20counting%20reads%20generated%20from%20either%20RNA%20or%20genomic%20DNA%20sequencing%20experiments.%20featureCounts%20implements%20highly%20efficient%20chromosome%20hashing%20and%20feature%20blocking%20techniques.%20It%20is%20considerably%20faster%20than%20existing%20methods%20(by%20an%20order%20of%20magnitude%20for%20gene-level%20summarization)%20and%20requires%20far%20less%20computer%20memory.%20It%20works%20with%20either%20single%20or%20paired-end%20reads%20and%20provides%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20options%20appropriate%20for%20different%20sequencing%20applications.%20AVAILABILITY%20AND%20IMPLEMENTATION:%20featureCounts%20is%20available%20under%20GNU%20General%20Public%20License%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Subread%20(http://subread.sourceforge.net)%20or%20Rsubread%20(http://www.bioconductor.org)%20software%20packages., Bioinformatics, 30, 7, 923%E2%80%93930, apr, 2014, http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btt656, en, 4</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref10"><unstructured_citation>STAR:%20ultrafast%20universal%20RNA-seq%20aligner, Dobin,%20Alexander%20and%20Davis,%20Carrie%20A%20and%20Schlesinger,%20Felix%20and%20Drenkow,%20Jorg%20and%20Zaleski,%20Chris%20and%20Jha,%20Sonali%20and%20Batut,%20Philippe%20and%20Chaisson,%20Mark%20and%20Gingeras,%20Thomas%20R, Cold%20Spring%20Harbor%20Laboratory,%20Cold%20Spring%20Harbor,%20NY,%20USA.%20dobin@cshl.edu, MOTIVATION:%20Accurate%20alignment%20of%20high-throughput%20RNA-seq%20data%20is%20a%20challenging%20and%20yet%20unsolved%20problem%20because%20of%20the%20non-contiguous%20transcript%20structure,%20relatively%20short%20read%20lengths%20and%20constantly%20increasing%20throughput%20of%20the%20sequencing%20technologies.%20Currently%20available%20RNA-seq%20aligners%20suffer%20from%20high%20mapping%20error%20rates,%20low%20mapping%20speed,%20read%20length%20limitation%20and%20mapping%20biases.%20RESULTS:%20To%20align%20our%20large%20(%3E80%20billon%20reads)%20ENCODE%20Transcriptome%20RNA-seq%20dataset,%20we%20developed%20the%20Spliced%20Transcripts%20Alignment%20to%20a%20Reference%20(STAR)%20software%20based%20on%20a%20previously%20undescribed%20RNA-seq%20alignment%20algorithm%20that%20uses%20sequential%20maximum%20mappable%20seed%20search%20in%20uncompressed%20suffix%20arrays%20followed%20by%20seed%20clustering%20and%20stitching%20procedure.%20STAR%20outperforms%20other%20aligners%20by%20a%20factor%20of%20%3E50%20in%20mapping%20speed,%20aligning%20to%20the%20human%20genome%20550%20million%202%20%5Ctimes%2076%20bp%20paired-end%20reads%20per%20hour%20on%20a%20modest%2012-core%20server,%20while%20at%20the%20same%20time%20improving%20alignment%20sensitivity%20and%20precision.%20In%20addition%20to%20unbiased%20de%20novo%20detection%20of%20canonical%20junctions,%20STAR%20can%20discover%20non-canonical%20splices%20and%20chimeric%20(fusion)%20transcripts,%20and%20is%20also%20capable%20of%20mapping%20full-length%20RNA%20sequences.%20Using%20Roche%20454%20sequencing%20of%20reverse%20transcription%20polymerase%20chain%20reaction%20amplicons,%20we%20experimentally%20validated%201960%20novel%20intergenic%20splice%20junctions%20with%20an%2080-90%25%20success%20rate,%20corroborating%20the%20high%20precision%20of%20the%20STAR%20mapping%20strategy.%20AVAILABILITY%20AND%20IMPLEMENTATION:%20STAR%20is%20implemented%20as%20a%20standalone%20C++%20code.%20STAR%20is%20free%20open%20source%20software%20distributed%20under%20GPLv3%20license%20and%20can%20be%20downloaded%20from%20http://code.google.com/p/rna-star/., Bioinformatics, 29, 1, 15%E2%80%9321, jan, 2013, http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/bts635, en, 1</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref11"><unstructured_citation>Track%20data%20hubs%20enable%20visualization%20of%20user-defined%20genome-wide%20annotations%20on%20the%20UCSC%20Genome%20Browser, Raney,%20Brian%20J%20and%20Dreszer,%20Timothy%20R%20and%20Barber,%20Galt%20P%20and%20Clawson,%20Hiram%20and